FBIS4-64260 "drweu084_h_94005" FBIS-WEU-94-084 Daily Report 30 Apr 1994 GERMANY Kremlin Reportedly Offers Bundeswehr 200 MiGs Kremlin Reportedly Offers Bundeswehr 200 MiGs LD3004094694 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 0637 GMT 30 Apr 94 LD3004094694 Berlin DDP/ADN German BFN [Text] Munich (DDP/ADN) -- The Bundeswehr may soon be flying over 200 MiG-29 fighters. The news magazine FOCUS reports that a Kremlin offer to this effect was put to the German Finance Ministry two weeks ago and was being examined. At present, 24 such aircraft were deployed from stocks of the GDR People's Army. Manfred Opel, the SPD [Social Democratic Party] defense expert, said the purchasing price totalled 4 billion marks. He said the amount could be deducted from the debts owed to Bonn by Moscow.
